WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.056
Desert sand is not one size — it is a whole mixture of

2
00:00:03.156 --> 00:00:07.031
grains, from dust to gravel. And no single binder holds all of them.

3
00:00:08.700 --> 00:00:11.434
Cementing — growing calcium carbonate — is superb

4
00:00:11.534 --> 00:00:14.268
on fine-to-medium grains. But it struggles on the

5
00:00:14.368 --> 00:00:16.697
very coarse ones and the very finest dust.

6
00:00:17.366 --> 00:00:19.753
This is where the other two prongs earn their

7
00:00:19.853 --> 00:00:23.179
place. The sticky gamma-P-G-A polymer grips the coarse grains,

8
00:00:23.279 --> 00:00:25.887
and the alginate gel catches the ultra-fine ones.

9
00:00:25.966 --> 00:00:28.754
Overlap all three and every grain size is held by at

10
00:00:28.854 --> 00:00:32.308
least one mechanism. That total coverage — not any single binder

11
00:00:32.408 --> 00:00:34.696
— is the whole point of using three prongs.

